{
  "stem": "4361.5",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "How should I translate it from Latin into a more acceptable term?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] I'll think about it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It means really it's the worst hole there is, which is an anal hole, all right.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's the hole of the anus, Anus Mundi.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Actually, Anus Mundi, it is the world's anus.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That's the exact translation.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So that was Lager C.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The quarantine was in Lager A, and after a number of weeks, those who made it during this time survived it, because one of the terrible things that was happening was diarrhea, which killed many of the young women.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Why diarrhea?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Because everybody was so terribly thirsty, and the water was polluted, and they drank water, and diarrhea took over.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then eventually, they were selected during [NON-ENGLISH] appells.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I was particularly lucky, I would say, because for some reason, my thirst stopped.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I didn't need to drink water, and I became constipated, as a matter of fact.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Until this day, when people tell me I should drink x number of glasses of water a day, I say to them, but you don't understand.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My lack of desire for water saved my life.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And so I was put at first in a work commando in Lager B, into another block, into another quarter.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I did all kind of work at first-- field work, carrying stones from one place to another, digging ditches, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Then I was selected one day to be part of a commando called The Brzezinka Commando, because the women were wearing white scarves, and I was put in the night working group to open those valises that we left on the train.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And that I did for about two months.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
